Zvaigžņotā nakts

The starry night, a canvas vast,
With jeweled dreams from ages past,
In silence wrapped, the world anew,
Oh, Zvaigžņotā nakts, we gaze at you.

Every twinkle holds a wish untold,
A tale of love, a memory bold,
In cosmic dance, our spirits soar,
In nature’s beauty, we seek more.

With hearts alight like solar flares,
The universe speaks in whispered prayers,
Oh, Zvaigžņotā nakts, shine bright and near,
In your embrace, we conquer fear.


- Rainis Jānis Pliekšāns
